finition of character in the <a href=3D"https://docs.microsoft.com/zh-cn/az=
ure/cognitive-services/speech-service/text-to-speech#pricing-note" aria-lab=
el=3D"Read the pricing note for details on billing for Speech to Text" data=
-bi-an=3D"faq-01" data-bi-tn=3D"undefined">pricing note</a>.</li>
        <li>For custom neural voice hosting: usage is billed per endpoint p=
er second. Check details in the <a href=3D"https://aka.ms/CNV-billing" aria=
-label=3D"Read the pricing note for details on billing for custom neural vo=
ice hosting" data-bi-an=3D"faq-01" data-bi-tn=3D"undefined">pricing note</a=
>.</li>
        <li>For personal voice profile storage: usage is billed per voice p=
rofile per day. Check details in the <a href=3D"https://aka.ms/PersonalVoic=
eBilling" aria-label=3D"Read the pricing note for details on billing for pe=
rsonal voice profile storage" data-bi-an=3D"faq-01" data-bi-tn=3D"undefined=
">pricing note</a>.</li>
        <li>For Text to Speech Avatar, usage is billed per second.</li>
        <li>For Speech to Text and Text to Speech (including Avatar), endpo=
int hosting for custom models is billed per second per model.</li>
    </ul>
</div>
        </li>
        <li class=3D"faq__item">
            <button type=3D"button" class=3D"faq__question" aria-expanded=
=3D"false" aria-controls=3D"718fe062" data-bi-slot=3D"2" data-bi-id=3D"faq-=
2" data-bi-an=3D"faq-01" data-bi-tn=3D"faq__question">


                What is a =E2=80=9CCustom Speech Model=E2=80=9D?
            </button>
            <div class=3D"faq__answer" id=3D"718fe062"><p>The Speech servic=
e enables users to adapt baseline models based on their own acoustic and la=
nguage data, leading to custom speech models that can be used against both =
Speech to Text and Speech Translation.</p></div>
        </li>
        <li class=3D"faq__item">
            <button type=3D"button" class=3D"faq__question" aria-expanded=
=3D"false" aria-controls=3D"b42f0d43" data-bi-slot=3D"3" data-bi-id=3D"faq-=
3" data-bi-an=3D"faq-01" data-bi-tn=3D"faq__question">


                What is a language model and why customize it?
            </button>
            <div class=3D"faq__answer" id=3D"b42f0d43"><p>The language mode=
l is a probability distribution over sequences of words. The language model=
 helps the system decide among sequences of words that sound similar, based=
 on the likelihood of the word sequences themselves. For example, =E2=80=9C=
recognize speech=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9Cwreck a nice beach=E2=80=9D sound al=
ike but the first hypothesis is far more likely to occur, and therefore wil=
l be assigned a higher score by the language model. If you expect voice que=
ries to your application to contain particular vocabulary items, such as pr=
oduct names or jargon that rarely occur in typical speech, it is likely tha=
t you can obtain improved performance by customizing the language model. Fo=
r example, if you were building an app to search MSDN by voice, it=E2=80=99=
s likely that terms like =E2=80=9Cobject-oriented=E2=80=9D or =E2=80=9Cname=
space=E2=80=9D or =E2=80=9Cdot net=E2=80=9D will appear more frequently tha=
n in typical voice applications. Customizing the language model will enable=
 the system to learn this.</p></div>
        </li>
        <li class=3D"faq__item">
            <button type=3D"button" class=3D"faq__question" aria-expanded=
=3D"false" aria-controls=3D"66fc27df" data-bi-slot=3D"4" data-bi-id=3D"faq-=
4" data-bi-an=3D"faq-01" data-bi-tn=3D"faq__question">


                What is an acoustic model and why customize it?
            </button>
            <div class=3D"faq__answer" id=3D"66fc27df"><p>The acoustic mode=
l is a classifier that labels short fragments of audio into one of several =
phonemes, or sound units, in each language. These phonemes can then be stit=
ched together to form words. For example, the word =E2=80=9Cspeech=E2=80=9D=
 is comprised of four phonemes =E2=80=9Cs p iy ch=E2=80=9D. These classific=
ations are made on the order of 100 times per second. Customizing the acous=
tic model can enable the system to learn to do a better job recognizing spe=
ech in atypical environments. For example, if you have an app designed to b=
e used by workers in a warehouse or factory, a customized acoustic model ca=
n more accurately recognize speech in the presence of the noises found in t=
hese environments.</p></div>
        </li>
        <li class=3D"faq__item">
            <button type=3D"button" class=3D"faq__question" aria-expanded=
=3D"false" aria-controls=3D"a2a97a6d" data-bi-slot=3D"5" data-bi-id=3D"faq-=
5" data-bi-an=3D"faq-01" data-bi-tn=3D"faq__question">


                What is a =E2=80=9CCustom Neural Voice=E2=80=9D?
            </button>
            <div class=3D"faq__answer" id=3D"a2a97a6d"><p>Speech service of=
fers a wide range of text-to-speech (TTS) voice fonts, however custom neura=
l voice allows you to build your own custom voice that suits your needs and=
 your brand. <a href=3D"https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/azure-ai/bui=
ld-a-natural-custom-voice-for-your-brand/ba-p/2112777" aria-label=3D"Read t=
he blog to learn more about creating custom neural voices in Speech service=
" data-bi-an=3D"faq-01" data-bi-tn=3D"undefined">Read the blog</a> for more=
 information.</p></div>
        </li>
        <li class=3D"faq__item">
            <button type=3D"button" class=3D"faq__question" aria-expanded=
=3D"false" aria-controls=3D"dafb359f" data-bi-slot=3D"6" data-bi-id=3D"faq-=
6" data-bi-an=3D"faq-01" data-bi-tn=3D"faq__question">


                What is language identification?
            </button>
            <div class=3D"faq__answer" id=3D"dafb359f"><p>Language identifi=
cation allows you to identify a switch in spoken language and transcribe sp=
eech accordingly. This can be applied in scenarios where the audio language=
 is unknown, or when speaker(s) may speak multiple languages. Single Langua=
ge Identification is available at no additional cost. Continuous Language I=
dentification is an enhanced add-on feature. <a href=3D"https://aka.ms/Spee=
ch/continuouslanguagedetection" aria-label=3D"Visit documentation link to l=
earn more about Language Identification" data-bi-an=3D"faq-01" data-bi-tn=
=3D"undefined">Visit docs</a> to learn more.</p></div>
        </li>
        <li class=3D"faq__item">
